Police are investigating the mysterious murder of a retired female teacher and her middle-aged son at Egoji area in South Imenti, Meru County. The woman identified as Tarasira Agnes and her son Mutwiri were hacked to death with their bodies being found with deep cuts on their heads. Area Chief Peter Njiru Gakiri said the incident was reported on Tuesday night at around 11pm in Gantune village. It is believed that the woman was first strangled before being hacked to death after raising an alarm during the attack. A nephew to the deceased said an axe was recovered at the murder scene. The chief suspects the incident might have been caused by land disputes as such cases are on a higher occurrence in the area. Also Read: Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis